n Milazzo due to lower discharge consumption than anticipated. Worth mentioning is that this was an Aframax cargo (abt. 80,0000 MT)  hence the vessel was far from fully loaded which obviously had a positive impact on the laden and port consumption and the port turnarounds. The increase in freight is explained by higher flat rate. Per main terms, freight was to be calculated basis Sicily laden/Messina ballast however further down in the main terms it says \u0022Rate to be calculated via west of Sicily laden and ballast provided such is the actual route performed by the vessel in ballast condition after having discharged ENI caro\u0022. As vessel\u0027s next cargo is loading in Turkey, vessel did in fact proceed west of Sicily thus the flate rate was increased with $0.43/mt improving the earnings with $61k."}],"offhireList":[{"id":198677,"dateStartUtc":null,"dateEndUtc":null,"days":null,"displayOrder":0,"offhireReason":null,"remark":null,"offhireBunkerList":[{"id":293970,"gradeName":"HSBF","quantity":null,"price":null,"displayOrder":0}]}],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}